Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
Project: Dynamic MERN Portfolio & Headless CMS
1. System Overview
The system is a fully dynamic, dual-application portfolio platform consisting of a public-facing frontend and a secured, headless-style administrative backend. Every text block, image, layout sequence, and design token is database-driven. The design will strictly avoid derivative "terminal" or standard "bento-box" themes, utilizing dynamic asymmetric grids, horizontal scroll timelines, and CMS-injected CSS variables for real-time theming.

2. Technology Stack (Strict)
Database: MongoDB (using Mongoose for Object Data Modeling).

Backend (API): Node.js with Express.js.

Frontend (Public & Admin): React.js (Next.js App Router recommended for SEO/SSR) with Tailwind CSS.

Language: Strict TypeScript (TS) across the entire monorepo.

State Management: Redux Toolkit (RTK) for Admin CMS; React Query for Public Frontend data fetching.

Media Storage: AWS S3 or Cloudinary (integrated via Multer).

3. Functional Requirements
3.1 Authentication & Security Module
FR-Auth-01: The system shall restrict access to the /admin/* routes using JWT (JSON Web Tokens).

FR-Auth-02: The system shall enforce a single Master Admin account; password must be hashed via bcrypt prior to database insertion.

FR-Auth-03: The API shall implement rate limiting on the public /api/contact endpoint (max 5 requests per IP per 15 minutes).

3.2 Content Management System (CMS) Module
FR-CMS-01 (Global Settings): The system shall provide an interface to update siteName, metaDescription, heroGreeting, primaryColor, secondaryColor, and resumeUrl.

FR-CMS-02 (Component Toggles): The system shall allow the admin to toggle the visibility of entire frontend sections (boolean switches for showExperience, showStartups, showCertifications).

FR-CMS-03 (CRUD Operations): The system shall allow Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations for:

Experiences: Including dynamic bullet points for responsibilities.

Projects: Including dynamic arrays for tech stacks and rich text for case studies.

Skills: Grouped dynamically by category names.

FR-CMS-04 (Drag-and-Drop Ordering): The system shall allow the admin to update the sortOrder integer of projects and experiences to dictate their render sequence on the frontend.

FR-CMS-05 (Media Upload): The system shall support image uploads for project thumbnails and startup logos, automatically compressing and storing the URL in the respective MongoDB document.

3.3 Public Frontend Rendering Module
FR-UI-01 (Dynamic Theming): The frontend shall fetch designTokens from the API on initial load and inject them into the CSS :root variables to instantly apply the admin's chosen color scheme.

FR-UI-02 (Empty State Handling): If an array (e.g., Projects) returns empty, or its visibility boolean is set to false, the frontend component must gracefully unmount without rendering blank containers.

FR-UI-03 (Form Submission): The frontend shall provide a Contact Form that POSTs to the database and alerts the admin via the CMS dashboard.

4. Database Schema & TypeScript Interfaces
Provide the following interfaces to the Agent to generate Mongoose schemas and strict types.

TypeScript
// 1. Global Settings & Profile
export interface IGlobalProfile extends Document {
  fullName: string;
  heroGreeting: string;
  heroTitles: string[];
  bioParagraphs: string[];
  designTokens: {
    primaryColor: string;
    secondaryColor: string;
    fontFamily: string;
  };
  socialLinks: {
    github: string;
    linkedin: string;
    email: string;
  };
  resumeUrl: string;
  sectionVisibility: {
    showStartups: boolean;
    showEducation: boolean;
    showSkills: boolean;
  };
}

// 2. Experience
export interface IExperience extends Document {
  roleTitle: string;
  organization: string;
  categoryType: 'Work' | 'Education' | 'Instruction' | 'Leadership';
  periodStart: Date;
  periodEnd: Date | null; // null = Present
  isActive: boolean;
  bulletPoints: string[];
  sortOrder: number;
}

// 3. Projects
export interface IProject extends Document {
  title: string;
  client: string;
  category: 'Enterprise' | 'Academic' | 'Startup';
  status: 'Delivered' | 'In Progress' | 'Planned';
  description: string;
  technologies: string[];
  repositoryUrl?: string;
  liveUrl?: string;
  thumbnailUrl?: string;
  sortOrder: number;
}

// 4. Startups & Ventures
export interface IStartup extends Document {
  brandName: string;
  role: string;
  philosophy: string;
  websiteUrl?: string;
  logoUrl?: string;
  isActive: boolean;
}
